2. Protocols

Protocol = Set of rules for communication.

Application-level protocols: HTTP, FTP, SMTP, POP, Telnet, SSH.

Transport-level: TCP, UDP.

Internet-level: IP.

ðŸ‘‰ Client & Server must use the same protocol.

Common Web Protocols

HTTP â€“ Web browsing (stateless).

FTP â€“ File transfer.

SMTP â€“ Email.

TCP/IP â€“ Base networking.

