4. Three Logical Layers

Presentation Logic

Display info, accept input.

HTML, CSS, JavaScript.

Business Logic

Data validation, processing.

Runs on server (Java, Node, etc.).

Persistence Logic

Storing and retrieving data.

Database servers (MySQL, Oracle, MongoDB).

5. HTTP Protocol
Request Format

Header

Method (GET, POST, PUT, DELETE)

URL, HTTP version

User-Agent (browser info)

Accept: MIME type

Content-Type

Cookies

Body â€“ Form data, JSON, etc.

wpt 2

Response Format

Header

Status Code (200 = OK, 400 = Client Error, 500 = Server Error, etc.)

Content-Type, Content-Length, Date, Cookies

Body â€“ HTML file or resource

wpt 2

6. Web Server vs Client

Web Server

Runs continuously, listens for requests.

Examples: Apache Tomcat, IIS, Express, JBoss, GlassFish.

Web Client

Browser or Postman.

Creates HTTP request, receives response, renders output

